In the theory of [[dynamical systems]] (or [[turbulence|turbulent flow]]), the '''Pomeau–Manneville scenario''' is the transition to chaos (turbulence) due to [[intermittency]].<ref>{{cite journal |first1=Yves |last1=Pomeau |first2=Paul |last2=Manneville |title=Intermittent Transition to Turbulence in Dissipative Dynamical Systems |journal=Commun. Math. Phys. |volume=74 |issue=2 |pages=189–197 |year=1980 |doi=10.1007/BF01197757|bibcode=1980CMaPh..74..189P }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |first=J.-P. |last=Eckmann |title=Roads to turbulence in dissipative dynamical systems |journal=Rev. Mod. Phys. |volume=53 |pages=643–654 |year=1981 |doi=10.1103/RevModPhys.53.643|bibcode=1981RvMP...53..643E }}</ref>

